Some old content as-is will be impossible.<br>
<br>
Most old content will be zergable if the only change is to cut the HP down... <br>
<br>
Some won't be.. ring of vulak... probably work fine as-is.. it's long, it's hard, but it's not mod rod dependant.  Might be a bit harder without mods, but it's not a one-mob encounter that requires a cheal rotation for an extended period.<br>
<br>
Emperor as-is cannot be killed without mod rods.  Not by any reasonable force... he simply cannot die fast enough.  Cut his HP to where LC or Wraith could drop him before the heal team goes OOM and he becomes zergable...<br>
<br>
NEW content designed from the ground up is different..  and VI could have the changes all ready to go...but their track record for making changes and thinking/testing them before dropping them on us is very bad.  <br>
<br>
Really the only reason I'm upset about this isn't a &quot;game balance&quot; issue and is totally self-centered.   My team has got Emp down finally, after months of farming keys/banes and a few  obligatory die-and-learn raids ... and they gonna change it.  That just sucks... (much like a soloing monk or MB-team wizard... balanced or not, it's like a kick to the ribs in the short term) <p>Gurunt Bangoo <Wraith>
