<br>
  Vi designed these mobs to be  HARD...  We as players have<br>
tried basically  everything  we can to kill the mobs in a fast,safe manner....<br>
<br>
  Complete heal rotation is  and  prolly always will be the most viable means of killing  most &quot;Boss&quot; type mobs because of the high damage output they have...  Sadly  rushing the mob like we  do against  Vox or  Naggy isn't a valid option..  These  mobs simply have too many hps and hit to hard for any one cleric to keep alive  whichever group member draws aggro..<br>
<br>
As to why  Mod rods became so popular?   It allowed  fewer people to  actually fight a &quot;Boss&quot; mob and have a  decent chance at winning...  or in the case of  Mobs Like  EMP, who's HPS and  Damage output is  such that the fight is taking 40-45 minutes, current mana regen just doesn't get the job done for a fight of this duration.....<br>
<br>
 I still honestly  believe most of you are missing the point , as to what  VI's true motives are....  I am of the opinion  VI  wants to  force us to   use more people to kill  the harder mobs in the game and in essense take skillz out of the equation,  where  20 ppl could take down Mob_01  due to mod rods being effective mana regen.  Now the same Mob might require  25-30 ppl...   <br>
  To everyone whom actually believes the tougher encounters are gonna be appropriately  re-tuned...   HAHAHAHAHA,  boy do i have some land to sell to you....  VI has always used the <br>
&quot;quote&quot;  Uber guilds to determine a zones  toughness or whether UberMob_00001  needs to be adjusted.......<br>
    I for one did spend all this time leveling to  60 and working my arse of to upgrade my gear, just to find i still need  30-80 ppl  to go kill the majority of the tougher mobs and nope i don't mean to trivilize these encounters, but for our relative power to mob power has grown weaker the higher in level we get as opposed to getting stronger.. But once  POP  comes out and  enough players  reach lvl 65...... i foresee   Kunark and  Velious  &quot;Boss&quot; mobs being upgraded because now they will be   Trivial to all the lvl 65 ppl.......  Much like the planes  where upgraded to deal with the new cap of lvl 60.... Now try going to planes with a raid force of mostly  lvls 46-50 and see whats happens...... The point is as we gain lvls and upgrade our gear, some encounters  should become  trivial,  hence VI releases  expansions to provide new challenges.... NOT retool old zones and force the lower lvls  to bury thier nose to the exp grind so that they can  gain the extra lvls  to be able to handle the new upgraded mobs...<br>
<br>
All in all it's the same song and dance from  VI......  <br>
<br>
We dont want you soloing!!!<br>
We dont want you to kill our  UBER Boss mob with under 30 ppl..<br>
We want to make you play longer and have less real chance at upgrades.....<br>
<br>
I challenge any of you to  prove me wrong on this......<br>
