<br>
Zerging in the traditional sense was pretty much described above, Where a cleric with a clickstick, and 50 people with to much experience to waste throw themselves at said uber-mob until either he dies, or you die (repeatedly). This &quot;tactic&quot; hasn't really been used lately by anyone I can remember, but back when people were still learning things, it worked - sorta.<br>
<br>
When people refer to Wraith or who ever as Zerg'ers its not really referring to the above defenition, but rather one of excess power in some people's eyes. Some mid-high end encounters don't take 50 people to kill, but using 50 people makes it easier/quicker. Some smaller guild take pride in killing say Aaaryonar or Statue with 20-30 people.  It makes things harder, increases the chances of something going wrong, but also makes for one helluva challenge in the end. <br>
<br>
Some encounters simply cannot be killed by the smaller guilds, no matter what tactics they employ if they cannot get a &quot;proper&quot; turnout of 50+ people. I recognize this.  When people call some guild Zerg'ers it's because 50+ people kill something which can be killed with 20-30 people. I'm not saying its a bad thing or that you couldn't do the same with the same numbers, it's just that you don't, because you do have the 50+ turnout.<br>
<br>
The smaller guys, take pride in killing more with less, I'm one of the smaller guys.<br>
<br>
Aaryonar and his two pets on the same pull Killed with 32 people - that was the proverbial shit. It was the challenge and the success that made it so.<br>
<br>
